Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine and potassium, with low total protein, CO₂, HDL cholesterol, and alkaline phosphatase. These findings suggest impaired renal function, possible mild metabolic acidosis, and mild hypoalbuminemia. Liver enzymes are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal insufficiency and monitoring of electrolyte and protein status.
